# Kili Design System

## Type Scale

Font sizes are defined in **two places that must stay in sync**:

- `frontend/tailwind.config.ts` ‚Üí `theme.extend.fontSize` ‚Äî generates the Tailwind utility classes and all responsive variants (`md:text-display`, etc.)
- `frontend/app/globals.css` ‚Üí `@theme` ‚Äî exposes the values as CSS custom properties (`var(--font-size-h1)`) for use in custom CSS

**To change a font size: edit the value in `tailwind.config.ts` and update the matching variable in `globals.css`.**

**Never use hardcoded `text-[Xrem]` or raw Tailwind size steps** ‚Äì use the named tokens instead.

| Token     | Value     | Tailwind class | When to use                         |
| --------- | --------- | -------------- | ----------------------------------- |
| `display` | 5 rem     | `text-display` | Hero h1 ‚Äì desktop                   |
| `h1`      | 3.5 rem   | `text-h1`      | Hero h1 ‚Äì mobile / page titles      |
| `h2`      | 3 rem     | `text-h2`      | Section headings ‚Äì desktop          |
| `h3`      | 2.25 rem  | `text-h3`      | Section headings ‚Äì mobile / card H1 |
| `h4`      | 1.5 rem   | `text-h4`      | Sub-headings / card titles          |
| `body-lg` | 1.125 rem | `text-body-lg` | Lead paragraphs / large body copy   |
| `body`    | 1 rem     | `text-body`    | Default body text                   |
| `sm`      | 0.875 rem | `text-sm`      | Secondary text, labels              |
| `xs`      | 0.75 rem  | `text-xs`      | Captions, badges, footnotes         |

**Responsive pattern:**

```tsx
// ‚úÖ correct ‚Äî mobile-first, scale up on md
<h1 className="text-h1 md:text-display">‚Ä¶</h1>
<h2 className="text-h3 md:text-h2">‚Ä¶</h2>

// ‚ùå wrong ‚Äî hardcoded arbitrary values
<h1 className="text-[3.5rem] md:text-[5rem]">‚Ä¶</h1>
```

To change the global type scale: **edit the CSS variables in `globals.css`**, not individual components.

