## Color Tokens

All colors use the Material You palette from `globals.css`. Use the semantic aliases:

| Tailwind class                | Use                                 |
| ----------------------------- | ----------------------------------- |
| `text-on-surface`             | Primary body text                   |
| `text-on-surface-variant`     | Secondary / muted text              |
| `text-primary`                | Brand-colored text and icons        |
| `text-on-primary`             | Text on primary-colored backgrounds |
| `bg-surface-container-lowest` | Card / form backgrounds             |
| `bg-primary`                  | Primary solid backgrounds           |
| `border-outline-variant`      | Subtle borders                      |

**Never use raw hex colors or Tailwind's default palette** (e.g. `text-slate-600`, `bg-indigo-700`) in new components ‚Äì map to a semantic token.

